==English==
===Etymology===
In the [[1800s]], there was an old method of placing small blocks of iron ore around a large furnace. The blocks of iron ore were called the "piglets," and the furnace was called the "pig." Since then, "pig iron" has become a widely used term. 

===Noun===
'''pig iron'''
#A type of [[iron ore]] shaped like a [[block]]. Pig iron is commonly used as a raw material in industry.

